※※
# delete-sky-workflow

Manually-run workflow that finds a `.sky` workflow by name and deletes it,
behind a manual approval gate. Pure bash + a wait — no LLM tokens. Three stages:

  find    — locate .sky/workflows/<name>.sky; fail (and list what's there) if absent
  confirm — manual gate: approve to delete, reject to keep
  remove  — delete the file

Run it:

  sky run delete-sky-workflow --var name="old-workflow"

  - name  kebab-case filename of the workflow to delete (no .sky extension)
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "delete-sky-workflow"
description = "Find a .sky workflow by name and delete it behind a manual approval gate. Fire via: sky run delete-sky-workflow --var name=<file>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※※
Step 1 — find. Resolves the target file. Exits non-zero (stopping the run) and
lists the available workflows when the name doesn't match.
※※

§find§
bash = "F=\".sky/workflows/$SKY_NAME.sky\"\nif [ ! -f \"$F\" ]; then\n  echo \"[delete] no workflow at $F\"\n  echo \"[delete] available:\"\n  ls .sky/workflows/ 2>/dev/null || true\n  exit 1\nfi\necho \"[delete] found $F\""
§§

※※
Step 2 — confirm. Manual gate. Deletion is irreversible, so a human approves
before the file is removed. Reject to stop; timeout after 1h.
※※

§confirm§
depends_on = ["find"]
wait.prompt = "Delete .sky/workflows/{{name}}.sky? Approve to remove it, reject to keep."
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.timeout = "1h"
§§

※※
Step 3 — remove. Deletes the file once approved.
※※

§remove§
depends_on = ["confirm"]
bash = "F=\".sky/workflows/$SKY_NAME.sky\"\nrm \"$F\" && echo \"[delete] removed $F\""
§§
